Title: The Last Rehearsal
Credit: Planning Example
Author: Scriptboard Example

# ACT I

INT. COMMUNITY THEATER - AFTERNOON

Director discovers the lead actor is gone hours before rehearsal.

> Goal: Keep the show alive.
> Problem: Nobody knows the full script.

INT. BACKSTAGE HALLWAY - AFTERNOON

The stage manager convinces a reluctant understudy to try.

# ACT II

INT. MAIN STAGE - EVENING

The understudy stumbles through the first run, then finds the rhythm.

> Midpoint: The performance begins to work.

INT. DRESSING ROOM - NIGHT

The understudy admits she never wanted the spotlight, only the craft.

# ACT III

INT. MAIN STAGE - NIGHT

Curtain up. The understudy walks into the light with total calm.

> Resolution: She owns the role.

FADE OUT.
